reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars BETTER THAN I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE !
reviews.reviewText: This S7P cordless vac replaces my Tineco which was @ 4 years old, I was having some issues with it. The Insevac is 2+ pounds lighter and stands up by itself which the Tineco didn't. Great suction power at 2 1/2 times less in price ! I also like the retractable tube. The replacement filters are at a good price point, I hope that they offer 4 or 6 packs in the future. There is one accessare I wish they offered.....A smaller motorized cleaning head for cleaning the floor mats in my car..........Love the vac so far.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great performance and value.
reviews.reviewText: Lightweight, easy to use, and maintain. Charger is fast, and batteries hold a good charge. Light enough to use one- handed. Power head is great for carpet and hard surface. Built-in headlight is good for under beds, sofas, etc. to see dust & dirt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Does what it is supposed to do.
reviews.reviewText: The Inse stick vacuum is easy to use and has great suction power.I was looking for a handheld vacuum for picking up small messes and that search kept bringing up stick vacuums. I had not really though of a stick vac but actually it can be just as convenient as a handheld vac for picking up stray litter around the litter box. It also works well as a car vacuum if you go at it with a fully charged battery.The Inse is lightweight and easy to maneuver. It stands by itself or can be hung from a small wall mount.I prefer a bagged vacuum for major house cleaning but for small mishaps it's kind of a hassle to drag out a heavier corded vac. I recommend a stick vacuum as backup, and for me the Inse is working great!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars In love with this vacuum
reviews.reviewText: To say I’m obsessed with this thing is an understatement. This stick vacuum has basically wiped out the need for a broom or my nice bissell vacuum. I’m so happy my sister told me about these vacuums, it’s made my OCD happy 😂
